before_start: {"blocks":[{"key":"djlv7","text":"Gather tools and set up the area and double check before beginning any surgical procedure. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
description: {"blocks":[{"key":"doqqj","text":"This protocol is to use for clearing blood from the brain and helping to maintain viable cells for electrophysiology experiments.  No PFA or any tools that have had contact with PFA should be used. This intracranial perfusion can help maintain viability of neurons in older animals and those who have undergone treatments that damage brain cells (for example: chronic methamphetamine and Parkinson's disease like treatments). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"ddeod","text":"The rat should be unable to feel pain, but still breathing so the neurons are as healthy and in a physiological condition close to when the animal was alive when you attempt to do electrophysiology experiments later using the brain slices. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"f081b","text":"when rat is lying down immobile, doesn’t right it’s position when moved, and is breathing slowly put isoflurane nose cone on rat and test for pain with forceps toe pinch of both feet","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fncnp","text":"inject into heart ventricle ~ 120 mL ice cold artificial cerebral spinal fluid, then ~ 120 mL ice cold high sucrose solution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"12cmo","text":"gently free brain from skull, cut cranial nerves when necessary","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"220gm","text":"let brain gently release from skull into ice cold high sucrose solution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4a0mj","text":"clean surgical tools carefully and let air dry","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"96u4k","text":"sharps disposed of in sharps biohazard red box","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dfraf","text":"let blood dissolve in bleach in flask in hood to decontaminate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e9363","text":"dispose of other biohazard material in a double bagged biohazard red bag .add sticker label. dispose of in biohazard waste bins.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"er4t9","text":"clean surfaces in hood with ethanol and paper towels","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"blo8u","text":"bring rat body in body bag with labeled tag to BSB 099 cold room","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2pnav","text":"bring cage and accessories with it to BSB dirty cage area for washing  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":69,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"a4d0e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"","data":{"amount":"","error":false,"guid":"4F7164A001E611ECB6378984844C02A5","id":"82675","label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}}}}
